column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Selling -  Weapons, Drones and Augments can be sold for 1/2 the purchasing price at stores. Click on the SELL tab at the top.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Great! I uploaded their location to your star map. I'm running out of options, so I have no choice but to trust you'll do what you have agreed to do. Added a quest marker to your map!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Take this bit of scrap as a down-payment. We'll use your jump signatures to follow you. You're really helping us out here. Added a quest marker to your map!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

You find two heavily damaged ships floating nearby, the remains of a battle. You begin to harvest some usable debris when you hear the sounds of someone beaming aboard followed by the shouts of a boarding party.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You happen upon an abandoned mining site. A few mining drones were left behind and could be repurposed.
You have arrived in Engi space. The Mantis have been threatening the Engi core worlds, but you should be able to stock up for your journey.
Thank you. Here, have this extra scrap as payment.
The civilian ship wisely made a fast retreat while you distracted the hostile ship.
An Engi ship hails: Engine upgrade necessary for travel home. Sale of equipment necessary for engine upgrade.

column11: At least you're confident, for what little that's worth. Here is their last known location. Added a quest marker to your map!
Scans reveal a number of asteroids with useful compositions. You extract some fuel.
You contact the delivery ship, who are grateful for your assistance. They offer you a reward for saving them.

You fire a few volleys but aren't able to penetrate the defense system's shields. Its weapons have no trouble piercing yours though, and you take minor damage before escaping. The station will need to find help elsewhere.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
As soon as you arrive a small Mantis ship detaches from a wreck and jumps away. You must have interrupted their salvage operation because you find a weapon ready to be installed!
Thank you, this will help greatly.
You've entered a poorly charted area of space that's known to be home to the Mantis. Ensure your hull plating is up to scratch and that you have enough fuel in the tank to make it through.
You fancy you see something moving in the shadow of the beacon, but all remains still.

You arrive to find yourself extremely close to a star. You receive a message from a pirate ship, I'm glad you arrived; our ship is damaged and we were getting desperate... I hope you don't mind if we take yours. Hostiles detected on board our ship!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The survivor gets on board the ship.

Uncertain about what you'll discover at this beacon, you scan the surroundings. You detect several warnings on wide-band channels discouraging any violence in protected trade-space. Perhaps you can find some wares nearby.

As soon as you arrive a small Mantis ship detaches from a wreck and jumps away. You must have interrupted their salvage operation because you find a weapon ready to be installed!

The Slugs developed on an ocean planet where the ability to telepathically sense another organism was more important than sight. Today they use this ability to navigate unfettered the depths of the nebulas they inhabit.
The Slug ship breaks apart and your systems return to normal. You collect what you can.

The wreckage is drifting faster than it first appeared. You barely avoid being pummeled by drifting wreckage - unable to detect anything of interest, you decide not to risk your ship and prepare to jump.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

There are a number of small stations for travellers in the area, lit up by guiding lights and advertisements. Only Slug ships are docked so you decide it's better to avoid a confrontation and steer clear.
The Slug ship breaks apart and your systems return to normal. You collect what you can.

You explore around the beacon and are shocked when a rock the size of a small moon suddenly looms ahead of you. Scans reveal the solid-looking rock is just a husk, almost entirely mined out of useful minerals.
A huge Slug teleports from nowhere onto the bridge! Before you can open fire, he's spread his wares across the helm and is brandishing things at you.
column12: System: teleporter, mind, hacking, Crew: Human, Slug, Engi,

column11: That isss... correct. You sssurprise me. Human, is it? Yesss... we can be partners. The Slug beams aboard and joins your crew!
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Slugs rely heavily on their telepathic powers and are reluctant to give up that advantage by extending beyond nebulas. It's unlikely you'll encounter any this far from the clouds.

There is only one other ship at this beacon, and it is showing heavy damage. You receive a message on your console: Greetings traveler. We were crippled by a band of pirates and are now forced to sell our remaining valuable equipment to acquire the necessary supplies to get home.

A few years ago this region was bustling with trade activity. Now it is overrun with bandits and marauders. You should tread lightly here.
Your ship detects a faint distress signal on a nearby moon. As you approach the rock, warning lights flash as hostiles beam aboard the ship from some hidden location.
You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
The refugee ship thanks you for your assistance. As a gesture of good will (and seeing how effectively you dispatched the enemy ship), they offer up what supplies they can spare.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The mercenary ship masks its jump signature to mimic your own and then jumps off in the opposite direction. This should keep the Rebels guessing.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You detect a hub of activity nearby. A large corporation has set up a trade depot and has a number of well armed ships patrolling. This appears to be a relatively safe place to get repairs.

column11: Great! I uploaded their location to your star map. I'm running out of options, so I have no choice but to trust you'll do what you have agreed to do. Added a quest marker to your map!

You make a good point. You traveled all the way out here to fulfill our request, despite what must have been... a difficult scenario to cause such a delay. Here, we'll even tip you for the inconvenience you must have gone through...
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You inform a nearby station of your flight from the Rebels. They offer to outfit your ship with a weapon and wish you well.
The Rock people have a particularly aggressive stance toward alien races trespassing in their space. You should tread carefully here.
You see a small trading post and ask about refuelling but they respond, Go away! We don't serve your kind here.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You cross paths with a Rock ship returning from a rare diplomatic mission. Equally surprising, the captain responds to your hails and agrees to a mutual trade.

column11: Tully responds, It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck.

column11: You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
